HELP!
OW OW OW! STOP IT!

What's that flickering light?
< looks around nervously >
Hey @MarsCuriosity... um... what are you up to?

Huh  it seems to be getting warmer. I guess summer is coming early!
My new robot friend really does have quite a steady  intimidating stare. I guess it's a cultural thing.
People tried to make me think you'd attack me  @MarsCuriosity. Haha! Me! I'm just an ordinary little Mars rock!
Oh! I think the robot heard me! It stopped moving  and it's looking at me again! It DOES want to be my friend! :)
Wait  @MarsCuriosity  don't leave! We could be friends!
Now the wheels are moving! Is it going to go away? Did I make it feel unwelcome?
My robot neighbor is making a sound! Maybe it's trying to communicate with me again! Hello! Helloooo!
My robot neighbor sure has an unsettling stare. If looks could kill...! Haha!
Starting to think maybe my new robot neighbor doesn't want to be my friend. Did I say something wrong?
My giant robot neighbor is still just staring fixedly at me. Starting to get a bit weird  haha!
Good morning  @MarsCuriosity! It looks like it's going to be a beautiful Sol today! Got any plans?
Only a few hours until sunrise and another beautiful Sol! Maybe today the mysterious robot and I will make a real connection. :)

Quiet night in Gale Crater with my enigmatic new robot friend. As I look up at the stars  I wonder: does my existence have a purpose?
Why would a giant machine rocket down from space just to shoot at me?
Wait  what? Lasers...?! Hang on  you guys are just messing with me. :) Haha!
Getting dark in the crater now. Hey @MarsCuriosity  are you sleeping? Big day tomorrow?

Huh. The big metal creature sure has a lot of equipment on its head. Maybe it's taking my picture! :)
Maybe I should try again to introduce myself. I'm sure the poor creature is just disoriented from being in a new place!
Okay  the big metal creature has stopped whirring now but the staring is getting a little uncomfortable...
Oo  it's making some kind of whirring sound now. Maybe it's trying to communicate with me! Hello!
The big metal creature is still just staring at me. I think maybe it's a little shy.
<putting best rock-face forward> I wish I could wave.
Oh  I think I've got the big metal creature's attention now -- it's looking right at me! Maybe it does want to be friends!
The big metal creature was scary at first  with the rockets and noise  but I'm sure it's just curious. Maybe I should say hello!
So much going on around here lately - the most excitement I've had in millions of years! But I'm glad it's back to normal now.
It's a beautiful Sol here in Gale Crater!

#Astro1:  During a solar eclipse the shadow of the moon races across the Earth.  Really  the Earth is rotating underneath it.
#Astro1: A lunar eclipse only occurs during full moon  a solar eclipse only during new moon. There are at least two of each per year.
#Astro1:  The moon's phases have nothing to do with the shadow of the Earth  but lunar eclipses do. Earth's shadow is red like the sunset.
#Astro1: The moon has a far side that we never see  because it rotates once per orbit. It is lit by the sun just as often as the near side.
#Astro1:  Pink Floyd got it right at the end of the album when they say  "There is no Dark Side of the Moon  really."
#Astro1:  I think modern science begins with Galileo  but there is room for debate -  it was a gradual process.
#Astro1: Full moon always rises at sunset  sets at sunrise  since the sun must be opposite in sky. Other phases rise/set at specific times.
#Astro1:  The seasons have nothing to do with the Earth's distance from the sun  they are all about the Earth's tilt relative to its orbit.
